subSubSection.paragraph:
Mesosoma
(
figure 24
). Length of mesosoma 1.3 times its maximal height; side of pronotum crenulate medially and anteriorly, remainder smooth, finely coriaceous ventrally; mesopleuron, mesosternum, metapleuron, mesoscutum, scutellum smooth and shiny; precoxal sulcus punctate only medially, smooth anteriorly and posteriorly; notauli deeply punctate anteriorly; scutellar sulcus with several carina posteriorly; propodeum medially convex, smooth and shiny with sparse long setae; metapleural flange absent (
figure 61
).

